-- Viacom Aims to Make Comedy Central Channel as One of Top 3 Global Brands
-- B y   J u n   Y a n g
-- 2012-03-07T06:14:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/viacom-aims-to-make-comedy-central-channel-as-one-of-top-3-global-brands.html
Viacom Inc., owner of MTV and
Paramount Pictures, said it aims to make its  Comedy Central 
channel one of its top three global brands along with the
Nickelodeon and MTV networks, as it seeks to lure more
television viewers worldwide.  “We’re making a big push with Comedy Central,” Robert
Bakish, chief executive officer of Viacom International Media
Networks, said in an interview in Seoul. “You’ll continue to
see additional Comedy Central products including in  Asia  in
2012. We’re on track to make Comedy our third great global
brand.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jun Yang in Seoul at 
 jyang180@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
